{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MDhwDwZ81z8MWxU99fNo9p","type":"tool_result","content":"500\t- [ ] `game.settled` handler registered in the event queue handler registry\n501\t- [ ] Handler iterates all players in the event payload\n502\t- [ ] Quest eligibility check runs before any progress/points/crate processing\n503\t- [ ] Active assignments loaded efficiently (indexed query on user_id + status = 'active')\n504\t- [ ] Progress updates are atomic: INSERT progress_event + UPDATE assignment.progress in one transaction\n505\t- [ ] Assignment status transitions to 'completed' when progress >= target\n506\t- [ ] Challenge completion emits reward intents through the same downstream path as other rewards (`points.grant` with `source_type = 'challenge_completed'`, or `crate.drop` with `trigger_type = 'challenge_completed'`)\n507\t- [ ] Points, crate, and pool-funding side-effects are emitted as separate reward events after challenge evaluation\n508\t- [ ] `game.settled` handler is idempotent for progress and reward-event emission; downstream reward handlers are independently idempotent\n509\t- [ ] Handler errors don't affect other players in the same event (per-player try/catch)\n510\t- [ ] Processing time per event is bounded (< 100ms target for the DB operations)\n511\t\n512\t---\n513\t\n514\t### FR-9: Completion Bonus\n515\t\n516\tA meta-reward for completing a set of challenges within a period. Primary use case: \"Complete all 3 daily challenges -> bonus crate.\"\n517\t\n518\t**Mechanics:**\n519\t- `completion_bonuses` row links to a campaign and specifies `required_count`\n520\t- After any assignment is marked completed, the engine counts completed assignments for that user in the same `period_key` and campaign\n521\t- If count >= `required_count` and no `bonus_completions` row exists for this user+bonus+period: mark bonus complete, trigger reward\n522\t\n523\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n524\t- [ ] Completion bonus check runs immediately after any assignment is marked completed\n525\t- [ ] Count query: `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM challenge_assignments WHERE user_id = ? AND period_key = ? AND status = 'completed' AND challenge_id IN (SELECT id FROM challenges WHERE campaign_id = ?)`\n526\t- [ ] Bonus completion is idempotent (UNIQUE on user_id, bonus_id, period_key)\n527\t- [ ] Bonus reward (crate or points) is triggered via the same reward path as challenge rewards\n528\t- [ ] Multiple bonuses can exist per campaign (future-proofing, but M1 has one per daily campaign)\n529\t\n530\t---\n531\t\n532\t### FR-10: Anti-Gaming & Quest Eligibility\n533\t\n534\tEvery game session is evaluated before counting toward challenge progress, points earning, or crate drops. In M1 this is intentionally lightweight: the only hard gate is refunded-game exclusion. We are explicitly not trying to ship a strong anti-abuse system until real usage gives us better signal.\n535\t\n536\t**`quest_eligible(event, player)` checks:**\n537\t1. Game settled normally (not refunded — `isWinner !== null`)\n538\t\n539\tIf the check fails, the game session is skipped for challenge progress, points, AND crate drops. The game still counts for normal gameplay (leaderboard, referral earnings, etc.) — only the reward system is gated.\n540\t\n541\t**Advisory fraud flags (optional, async, non-blocking):**\n542\t| Signal | Action |\n543\t|---|---|\n544\t| 5+ challenge completions in < 10 minutes | Create `fraud_flags` row, type: `velocity`, review only |\n545\t| Same repeated opponent pattern across a recent sample | Create `fraud_flags` row, type: `repeated_opponent`, review only |\n546\t| SOL crate drop for already-flagged user | Optional hold for manual review if ops decides to turn it on |\n547\t\n548\tFraud flags are draft-level operator signals in M1. They should not block normal progress or payouts unless an explicit operator policy is added later.\n549\t\n550\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n551\t- [ ] `quest_eligible()` function implemented and called before all reward processing\n552\t- [ ] Refunded games (`isWinner === null`) are excluded from challenge progress, points, and crate drops\n553\t- [ ] Non-refund games continue through normal challenge/reward flow with no additional M1 gating\n554\t- [ ] Ineligible games still settle normally (no impact on core game loop)\n555\t- [ ] Any fraud flags implemented in M1 are advisory-only and do not silently change reward behavior\n556\t\n557\t---\n558\t\n559\t### FR-11: Daily & Weekly Challenge Assignment\n560\t\n561\tPlayers receive a set of challenges at each reset. Challenges are drawn from the pool of active challenge templates in the relevant campaign.\n562\t\n563\t**Daily (00:00 UTC):**\n564\t- 3 challenges drawn from the \"Daily\" campaign's active challenge pool\n565\t- Fixed for M1: all players get the same 3 — selected as the top N active challenges by `sort_order ASC` (deterministic, operator-controlled via admin API). Rotation is M2.\n566\t- Assignments expire at next daily reset (24h)\n567\t\n568\t**Weekly (Monday 00:00 UTC):**\n569\t- 2 challenges drawn from the \"Weekly\" campaign's active challenge pool\n570\t- Fixed for M1: all players get the same 2 — selected as the top N active challenges by `sort_order ASC`\n571\t- Assignments expire at next weekly reset (7d)\n572\t\n573\t**Assignment mechanics:**\n574\t- M1 uses lazy assignment only: on first `GET /challenges/mine` call after reset, if no assignments exist for the current period, generate them for that user\n575\t- No bulk reset-time assignment worker in M1\n576\t- Expired assignments (past `expires_at`, still `active`) are transitioned to `expired` at query time or by a lightweight cleanup worker\n577\t- Deactivating a challenge template does not affect existing assignments — players keep their in-progress work for the current period\n578\t\n579\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n580\t- [ ] Daily challenges assigned lazily on first `GET /challenges/mine` call after 00:00 UTC\n581\t- [ ] Weekly challenges assigned lazily on first call after Monday 00:00 UTC\n582\t- [ ] `period_key` format: `daily:YYYY-MM-DD` for dailies, `weekly:YYYY-WNN` for weeklies\n583\t- [ ] Assignment count matches campaign config (3 daily, 2 weekly for M1)\n584\t- [ ] Challenges drawn from active challenges in the appropriate campaign\n585\t- [ ] UNIQUE constraint prevents duplicate assignments for same user+challenge+period\n586\t- [ ] Expired assignments are marked `expired` (either at query time or by cleanup worker)\n587\t- [ ] Completion bonus for the daily campaign is checked when 3rd daily is completed\n588\t\n589\t---\n590\t\n591\t### FR-12: Onboarding Quest Chain\n592\t\n593\tA one-time sequential challenge flow for new players. Uses `prerequisite_id` to enforce ordering.\n594\t\n595\t**Steps:**\n596\t1. \"Play your first game\" — `{action: game_completed, scope: any, threshold: 1, reward: 1000 points}`\n597\t2. \"Win a game\" — `{action: game_won, scope: any, threshold: 1, reward: 1500 points, prerequisite: step 1}`\n598\t3. \"Try all 3 game types\" — `{action: game_completed, scope: any, condition: unique_game_types, threshold: 3, reward: 2500 points + crate, prerequisite: step 2}`\n599\t\n600\t**Mechanics:**\n601\t- Onboarding campaign with `campaign_type = 'onboarding'`\n602\t- Assignments created lazily on first `GET /challenges/mine` call (if user has no onboarding assignments)\n603\t- Only the first step (no prerequisite) is assigned initially\n604\t- When a step completes, the next step (whose `prerequisite_id` matches the completed challenge) is automatically assigned\n605\t- Onboarding challenges never expire\n606\t- Once all steps are completed, onboarding is done — no repeat\n607\t\n608\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n609\t- [ ] Onboarding campaign and 3 challenge templates seeded in migration or seed script\n610\t- [ ] First onboarding step assigned on first `GET /challenges/mine` call for new users\n611\t- [ ] Completing a step auto-assigns the next step (by `prerequisite_id`)\n612\t- [ ] Onboarding assignments have `period_key = 'onboarding'` and no `expires_at`\n613\t- [ ] Onboarding is one-time: once all steps completed, no further assignments\n614\t- [ ] Onboarding challenges appear in `GET /challenges/mine` alongside daily/weekly\n615\t\n616\t---\n617\t\n618\t### FR-13: Reward Configuration\n619\t\n620\tAll economy parameters stored in `reward_config` table, readable by the engine at evaluation time, updatable via admin API.\n621\t\n622\t**Default seed values:**\n623\t\n624\t| Key | Default | Description |\n625\t|---|---|---|\n626\t| `points_per_dollar` | `500` | Base points per $1 USD wagered |\n627\t| `dogpile_default_multiplier` | `2.0` | Default multiplier for new Dogpile events |\n628\t| `reward_pool_fee_share` | `0.20` | Fraction of fees routed to reward pool |\n629\t| `points_crate_drop_rate` | `0.05` | 5% chance per player per settled game |\n630\t| `sol_crate_drop_rate` | `0.01` | 1% chance per player per settled game |\n631\t| `sol_crate_pool_pct` | `0.10` | SOL crate pays 10% of pool balance |\n632\t| `sol_crate_min_value` | `10000000` | 0.01 SOL minimum (below = suppress) |\n633\t| `points_crate_min` | `500` | Minimum points in a points crate |\n634\t| `points_crate_max` | `5000` | Maximum points in a points crate |\n635\t| `daily_challenge_count` | `3` | Challenges assigned per daily reset |\n636\t| `weekly_challenge_count` | `2` | Challenges assigned per weekly reset |\n637\t\n638\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n639\t- [ ] `reward_config` table seeded with all defaults above in the migration\n640\t- [ ] Config values read by the engine at evaluation time (not cached beyond a single handler invocation)\n641\t- [ ] Admin API endpoint `PUT /admin/reward-config/:key` updates a config value\n642\t- [ ] Admin API endpoint `GET /admin/reward-config` returns all config values\n643\t- [ ] Admin endpoints require operator auth (existing auth middleware or admin-only check)\n644\t- [ ] Invalid config keys rejected (400)\n645\t- [ ] Config change takes effect on next `game.settled` event (no restart needed)\n646\t\n647\t---\n648\t\n649\t### FR-14: Player-Facing API Endpoints\n650\t\n651\tAPI for the frontend to display challenges, progress, points, and crate history.\n652\t\n653\tPlayer-facing note: all challenge and reward updates are async from `game.settled`. Progress, points, and crate history should appear within seconds after settlement, but are not guaranteed to be visible in the same request path that triggered settlement.\n654\t\n655\t**Endpoints:**\n656\t\n657\t| Method | Path | Description |\n658\t|---|---|---|\n659\t| `GET` | `/challenges/mine` | Returns active + recently completed challenges for the authenticated user. Triggers lazy assignment if needed. |\n660\t| `GET` | `/challenges/mine/history` | Paginated list of past challenge completions |\n661\t| `GET` | `/points/mine` | Returns current point balance and lifetime earned |\n662\t| `GET` | `/points/mine/history` | Paginated points ledger history from `point_grants` |\n663\t| `GET` | `/crates/mine` | Paginated crate drop history with `status` (`pending`, `granted`, `failed`) |\n664\t| `GET` | `/dogpile/current` | Returns current/next Dogpile event (if any) with countdown to start or end |\n665\t| `GET` | `/dogpile/schedule` | Returns upcoming Dogpile events |\n666\t\n667\t**`GET /challenges/mine` response shape:**\n668\t```typescript\n669\t{\n670\t  daily: {\n671\t    challenges: Array<{\n672\t      id: number;\n673\t      title: string;\n674\t      description: string;\n675\t      progress: number;\n676\t      target: number;\n677\t      status: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"expired\";\n678\t      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n679\t      completedAt: string | null;\n680\t    }>;\n681\t    bonus: {\n682\t      title: string;\n683\t      required: number;\n684\t      completed: number;\n685\t      status: \"active\" | \"completed\";\n686\t      reward: { type: \"points\" | \"crate\"; amount?: number };\n687\t    } | null;\n688\t    resetsAt: string;  // ISO 8601\n689\t  };\n690\t  weekly: {\n691\t    /* same shape; `bonus` is `null` in M1 unless a weekly completion bonus is explicitly configured */\n692\t  };\n693\t  onboarding: {\n694\t    steps: Array<{ /* same shape + locked: boolean */ }>;\n695\t    completed: boolean;\n696\t  } | null;  // null after onboarding complete\n697\t}\n698\t```\n699\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9711a7e-4153-4e8b-be5f-32a94d4f2fda","uuid":"87b1674a-4f67-48ee-b3eb-35206208fe51","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:18:09.009Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/400-challenge-engine/spec.md","content":"- [ ] `game.settled` handler registered in the event queue handler registry\n- [ ] Handler iterates all players in the event payload\n- [ ] Quest eligibility check runs before any progress/points/crate processing\n- [ ] Active assignments loaded efficiently (indexed query on user_id + status = 'active')\n- [ ] Progress updates are atomic: INSERT progress_event + UPDATE assignment.progress in one transaction\n- [ ] Assignment status transitions to 'completed' when progress >= target\n- [ ] Challenge completion emits reward intents through the same downstream path as other rewards (`points.grant` with `source_type = 'challenge_completed'`, or `crate.drop` with `trigger_type = 'challenge_completed'`)\n- [ ] Points, crate, and pool-funding side-effects are emitted as separate reward events after challenge evaluation\n- [ ] `game.settled` handler is idempotent for progress and reward-event emission; downstream reward handlers are independently idempotent\n- [ ] Handler errors don't affect other players in the same event (per-player try/catch)\n- [ ] Processing time per event is bounded (< 100ms target for the DB operations)\n\n---\n\n### FR-9: Completion Bonus\n\nA meta-reward for completing a set of challenges within a period. Primary use case: \"Complete all 3