{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014YfCnAqEH2k1MF6gv677Nm","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Event Handler Registration Pattern Report\n\n### 1. Event Type Constants\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\nThe event types are defined as a const object with a derived union type for compile-time safety:\n\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\nThis pattern ensures typos are compile-time errors instead of dead events at runtime.\n\n### 2. Handler Registration Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n\nThe handler registry uses a Map-based dispatcher with one handler per event type (no pub/sub fan-out):\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (payload: Record<string, unknown>) => Promise<void>;\n\nconst handlers = new Map<string, EventHandler>();\n\nexport function registerHandler(eventType: EventType, handler: EventHandler): void {\n  handlers.set(eventType, handler);\n}\n\nexport function getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined {\n  return handlers.get(eventType);\n}\n\nexport function clearHandlers(): void {\n  handlers.clear();\n}\n```\n\n**Key design points**:\n- Handlers are idempotent (re-processing is a safe no-op)\n- One handler per event type\n- Test isolation via `clearHandlers()`\n\n**Registration in application**:\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 206-209)\n\nCurrently, only one handler is registered:\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n```\n\nThe handler is registered **before** starting the event queue worker.\n\n### 3. Event Queue Worker Dispatch Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\nThe worker:\n- Polls the `event_queue` table at configurable intervals (default: 1500ms)\n- Claims events atomically using `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` for safe concurrency\n- Looks up handler via `getHandler(event.event_type)`\n- Marks unhandled event types as `dead` immediately with warning log\n- Implements exponential backoff on failures:\n  - Attempt 1 failure → retry after 5 seconds\n  - Attempt 2 failure → retry after 30 seconds\n  - Attempt 3+ failure → retry after 300 seconds (5 minutes)\n- After max attempts (default: 3), event marked as `dead`\n\n### 4. Test Setup/Teardown Patterns\n\n**Integration Test**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\n**Table Truncation** (line 397):\n```sql\nTRUNCATE rounds, closecall_rounds, closecall_candles, operator_events, event_queue, \n         game_entries, transactions, player_profiles, referral_codes, referral_links, \n         referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE\n```\n\n**Lifecycle**:\n- `beforeAll`: Creates DB connection and mock Solana Connection, builds Hono app\n- `beforeEach`: \n  - Truncates all game-related tables with `RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`\n  - Resets PlatformConfig cache\n  - Creates fresh mock Connection\n  - Pre-populates mock with entropy and config accounts\n- `afterAll`: Closes DB and SQL connections\n\n**Queue Test**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts`\n\n**Lifecycle**:\n- `beforeAll`: Creates postgres connection\n- `beforeEach`: `TRUNCATE event_queue RESTART IDENTITY`\n- `afterAll`: Closes SQL connection\n\n**Queue Integration Test**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts`\n\n**Lifecycle**:\n- `beforeAll`: Creates postgres connection\n- `beforeEach`: \n  - `TRUNCATE event_queue RESTART IDENTITY`\n  - `clearHandlers()` for handler isolation\n- `afterAll`: Closes SQL connection\n\n### 5. Event Emission Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\nEvents are emitted within database transactions to ensure atomic commitment:\n\n```typescript\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }>\n```\n\n- **Must be called within a transaction** (`sql.begin()`)\n- **Options**: `maxAttempts` (default: 3), `scheduledAt` (default: now)\n- Returns `eventId` as a `bigint`\n\n### 6. Handler Implementation Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`\n\nFactory pattern that accepts dependencies:\n\n```typescript\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Handler implementation\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotency Design**:\n- Checks claim status early (`completed` → skip, `failed` → skip)\n- Transient errors set status to `error` (retryable)\n- Permanent failures set status to `failed` (no more retries)\n- Only rethrows transient errors to trigger queue worker retry logic\n\n**Key Files Summary**:\n- Event types: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n- Registry/dispatcher: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n- Worker/polling: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n- Event emission: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n- Handler registration: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (line 206)\n- Referral claim handler: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9711a7e-4153-4e8b-be5f-32a94d4f2fda","uuid":"61933b3b-35f2-48ce-8ac0-5ea6e91a1c1b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:20:01.840Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the event handler registration pattern in the rng-utopia backend. Please:\n\n1. Read `backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts` to see all existing event types\n2. Read the event handler registry/dispatcher - look for how handlers are registered for event types (check files in `backend/services/backend/src/queue/` or similar)\n3. Read `backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` to understand the testing patterns used (especially table truncation, DB setup, etc.)\n\nReport: event type constants, handler registration pattern, test setup/teardown patterns, table truncation list.","agentId":"a569dc0416e45eea1","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Event Handler Registration Pattern Report\n\n### 1. Event Type Constants\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\nThe event types are defined as a const object with a derived union type for compile-time safety:\n\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payou