y after 30 seconds\n  - Attempt 3+ failure → retry after 300 seconds (5 minutes)\n- After max attempts (default: 3), event marked as `dead`\n\n### 4. Test Setup/Teardown Patterns\n\n**Integration Test**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\n**Table Truncation** (line 397):\n```sql\nTRUNCATE rounds, closecall_rounds, closecall_candles, operator_events, event_queue, \n         game_entries, transactions, player_profiles, referral_codes, referral_links, \n         referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE\n```\n\n**Lifecycle**:\n- `beforeAll`: Creates DB connection and mock Solana Connection, builds Hono app\n- `beforeEach`: \n  - Truncates all game-related tables with `RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`\n  - Resets PlatformConfig cache\n  - Creates fresh mock Connection\n  - Pre-populates mock with entropy and config accounts\n- `afterAll`: Closes DB and SQL connections\n\n**Queue Test**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts`\n\n**Lifecycle**:\n- `beforeAll`: Creates postgres connection\n- `beforeEach`: `TRUNCATE event_queue RESTART IDENTITY`\n- `afterAll`: Closes SQL connection\n\n**Queue Integration Test**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts`\n\n**Lifecycle**:\n- `beforeAll`: Creates postgres connection\n- `beforeEach`: \n  - `TRUNCATE event_queue RESTART IDENTITY`\n  - `clearHandlers()` for handler isolation\n- `afterAll`: Closes SQL connection\n\n### 5. Event Emission Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\nEvents are emitted within database transactions to ensure atomic commitment:\n\n```typescript\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }>\n```\n\n- **Must be called within a transaction** (`sql.begin()`)\n- **Options**: `maxAttempts` (default: 3), `scheduledAt` (default: now)\n- Returns `eventId` as a `bigint`\n\n### 6. Handler Implementation Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`\n\nFactory pattern that accepts dependencies:\n\n```typescript\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Handler implementation\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotency Design**:\n- Checks claim status early (`completed` → skip, `failed` → skip)\n- Transient errors set status to `error` (retryable)\n- Permanent failures set status to `failed` (no more retries)\n- Only rethrows transient errors to trigger queue worker retry logic\n\n**Key Files Summary**:\n- Event types: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n- Registry/dispatcher: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n- Worker/polling: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n- Event emission: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n- Handler registration: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (line 206)\n- Referral claim handler: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`"}],"totalDurationMs":92653,"totalTokens":48778,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":264,"cache_read_input_tokens":46726,"output_tokens":1783,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":264},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DLCZkRdkuczBhBea5KEi7X","type":"tool_result","content":"    pdaWatcher.unwatch(pda); // clean up subscription after settlement\n  },\n  isFinalized: (pda) => retrySettler.isFinalized(pda),\n});\nworker.start();\n\n// Close Call clock worker — fetches boundary prices + settles open rounds\n// Rounds are created on-demand by players via /closecall/bet\nconst closeCallClock = createCloseCallClockWorker({\n  connection,\n  serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair,\n  db,\n});\ncloseCallClock.start();\n\n// Register event handlers before starting the worker\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n\n// Event queue worker — processes async side-effects (rewards, notifications, etc.)\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\nlogger.info(\"Event queue worker started\", {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\n\n// Game-specific routes\napp.route(\n  \"/coinflip\",\n  createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair, pdaWatcher }),\n);\napp.route(\n  \"/lord\",\n  createLordRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair, pdaWatcher }),\n);\n\n// Close Call — JWT + rate limiting on POST /bet (co-signs with server keypair)\napp.use(\n  \"/closecall/bet\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret }),\n);\napp.use(\n  \"/closecall/bet\",\n  createRateLimitMiddleware({\n    perWallet: config.rateLimitPerWallet,\n    global: config.rateLimitGlobal,\n    windowMs: 60_000,\n  }),\n);\n\n// Close Call routes (read endpoints are public, /bet is auth'd above)\napp.route(\"/closecall\", createCloseCallRoutes({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair,\n  clockWorker: closeCallClock,\n}));\n\n// Leaderboard routes — public, no auth\napp.route(\"/leaderboard\", createLeaderboardRoutes({ db }));\n\n// Price routes — public, no auth\napp.route(\"/price\", createPriceRoutes());\n\n// Round verification routes\napp.route(\"/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({ db }));\n\n// Health endpoint — wired after worker exists so we can query its status\napp.route(\n  \"/health\",\n  createHealthRoutes({\n    db,\n    sql,\n    isWorkerRunning: () => worker.isRunning,\n  }),\n);\n\n// Internal admin routes — only registered when ADMIN_TOKEN is set (dev/devnet only)\nif (config.adminToken) {\n  app.route(\"/internal\", createInternalRoutes({ config, sql }));\n  logger.warn(\"Admin routes enabled at /internal — do NOT set ADMIN_TOKEN in production\");\n}\n\nconst port = config.port;\nlogger.info(\"fairness-backend started\", { port });\n\nserve({\n  fetch: app.fetch,\n  port,\n  hostname: \"0.0.0.0\",\n});\n\nexport default {\n  port,\n  fetch: app.fetch,\n};","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011FEtT5pmcUxxcCPKx2ap8f","session_id":"c9711a7e-4153-4e8b-be5f-32a94d4f2fda","uuid":"16cf7801-3bb7-4120-8f3e-9beec4fbc33f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:20:13.979Z"}
