{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011FEtT5pmcUxxcCPKx2ap8f","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Backend Migration Pattern Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the rng-utopia backend migration system. Here's the comprehensive report:\n\n### File Paths and Locations\n\n**Migrations Directory:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/`\n\n**Migration Runner:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`\n\n**Package Scripts:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/package.json`\n\n### Current Migration Files (Latest: 010)\n\n1. `001_init.sql` — Rounds table (coinflip + lord/jackpot)\n2. `002_operator_events.sql` — Operator audit log\n3. `003_auth.sql` — JWT challenge-response + refresh tokens\n4. `004_closecall_rounds.sql` — Close Call pari-mutuel rounds\n5. `005_closecall_candles.sql` — Cached minute-boundary BTC prices\n6. `006_player_profiles.sql` — Player identity & profile\n7. `007_game_entries.sql` — Single source of truth for participation + stats\n8. `008_transactions.sql` — Real on-chain SOL movements\n9. `009_event_queue.sql` — Postgres-backed async event queue\n10. `010_referral.sql` — Referral system (codes, links, earnings, claims, KOL rates)\n\n**We are at version 010 (the latest migration number).**\n\n### Naming Conventions\n\n**Format:** `NNN_description.sql` where NNN is a zero-padded 3-digit version number\n\n**Pattern:** Numbers are parsed strictly as the first part of the filename before underscore. Files must be properly sorted alphanumerically.\n\n**Command Structure:** Run migrations via:\n- `npm run migrate` — applies pending migrations\n- `npm run migrate:status` — shows applied/pending status\n- `npm start` — automatically runs migrations before starting the server\n\n### Migration System Architecture\n\n**Runner Location:** `migrate.ts` uses `postgres` package (raw SQL with typed results)\n\n**Key Concepts:**\n- Migrations are tracked in a `_migrations` table (version INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ)\n- Each migration runs inside a transaction (atomicity guaranteed)\n- Idempotent: re-running skips already-applied files\n- No down migrations (unidirectional only)\n- Migrations run via `sql.unsafe(content)` + `sql.begin()` for transactional safety\n\n**Startup Flow:**\n```\nnpm start → src/migrate.ts (auto-run) → src/index.ts (server startup)\n```\n\n### SQL Style & Conventions\n\n**Identity Columns:**\n```sql\nBIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n```\nUsed instead of BIGSERIAL for explicit generation.\n\n**UUID Columns:**\n```sql\nUUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()\n```\nUsed in referral_claims table.\n\n**Timestamps:**\n```sql\nTIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()  — all timestamps use timezone-aware\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- CHECK constraints on enum TEXT columns for validation (e.g., `CHECK (phase IN ('open', 'settled', 'refunded'))`)\n- Unique constraints with names (e.g., `CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round UNIQUE (...)`)\n- Foreign key relationships NOT used (design pattern: reference by ID text)\n\n**Indexing Patterns:**\n- Filtered indexes for performance: `CREATE INDEX ... WHERE status IN ('pending', 'processing')`\n- Composite indexes for queries: `(user_id, created_at DESC)`\n- BRIN indexes for time-series data: `USING BRIN (minute_ts)`\n- Unique conditional indexes: `CREATE UNIQUE INDEX ... WHERE status IN (...)`\n\n**Example (from 007_game_entries):**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE game_entries (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  wallet          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  game            TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (game IN ('coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')),\n  round_pda       TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  match_id        TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL CHECK (amount_lamports > 0),\n  side            TEXT,\n  is_winner       BOOLEAN,\n  payout_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  UNIQUE (wallet, round_pda)\n);\n```\n\n### Seed Data Patterns\n\n**No seed data exists in migrations.** The project follows these patterns instead:\n\n1. **Auto-creation on first use:** Player profiles are auto-created on first JWT auth via application code (not migrations)\n2. **Event-driven:** Configuration and platform parameters read from on-chain `PlatformConfig` PDA at settlement time (not seeded in DB)\n3. **No INSERT statements:** All 10 migration files use CREATE TABLE/INDEX only—zero INSERT statements\n4. **Dynamic initialization:** Tables like `closecall_candles` and `event_queue` are populated by async workers (pda-watcher, closecall-clock, event-worker) after schema creation\n\n### Database Schema Constants\n\n- **Engine:** PostgreSQL 16\n- **Amounts:** All stored in lamports (u64), conversion to SOL only at display boundaries\n- **User identity:** user_id (TEXT), wallet (TEXT) with separate unique constraints\n- **Rate fields:** Integer basis points (bps) for fees and rates\n- **PDA references:** TEXT (not foreign keys)—matches Solana account addresses\n\n### Summary for Next Migration\n\nWhen creating migration 011, follow this template:\n\n```sql\n-- 011_feature_name.sql — Description of what this adds.\n\nCREATE TABLE [new_table] (\n  id                 BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  [field_name]       TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK ([field_name] IN ('value1', 'value2')),\n  [timestamp_field]  TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  created_at         TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_[table]_[field] ON [new_table] ([field], created_at DESC);\nCREATE INDEX idx_[table]_[field]_filtered ON [new_table] ([field]) WHERE [condition];\n```\n\nKey points: zero-padded version number, CHECK constraints for enums, GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY, TIMESTAMPTZ for all dates, comment header with purpose."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9711a7e-4153-4e8b-be5f-32a94d4f2fda","uuid":"014261d7-b248-4ae4-a184-15a78cc1102b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:20:46.021Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the backend migration patterns for the rng-utopia project. Please:\n\n1. List all existing migration files in `backend/services/backend/migrations/` (or wherever migrations live)\n2. Read the most recent migration file to understand the conventions used (naming, SQL style, etc.)\n3. Check what migration number we're at (latest file number)\n4. Read the DB client file at `backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` to understand how migrations run\n5. Look for any seed data patterns in existing migrations\n\nReport: file paths, naming conventions, SQL style (CHECK constraints, IDENTITY columns, etc.), and how seeds are done.","agentId":"a021da408df945a52","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Backend Migration Pattern Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the rng-utopia backend migration system. Here's the comprehensive report:\n\n### File Paths and Locations\n\n**Migrations Directory:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/`\n\n**Migration Runner:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`\n\n**Package Scripts:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/package.json`\n\n### Current Migration Files (Latest: 010)\n\n1. `001_init.sql` — Rounds table (coinflip + lord/jackpot)\n2. `002_operator_events.sql` — Operator audit log\n3. `003_auth.sql` — JWT challenge-response + refresh tokens\n4. `004_closecall_rounds.sql` — Close Call pari-mutuel rounds\n5. `005_closecall_candles.sql` — Cached minute-boundary BTC prices\n6. `006_player_profiles.sql` — Player identity & profile\n7. `007_game_entries.sql` — Single source of truth for participation + stats\n8. `008_transactions.sql` — Real on-chain SOL movements\n9. `009_event_queue.sql` — Postgres-backed async event queue\n10. `010_referral.sql` — Referral system (codes, links, earnings, claims, KOL rates)\n\n**We are at version 010 (the latest migration number).**\n\n### Naming Conventions\n\n**Format:** `NNN_description.sql` where NNN is a zero-padded 3-digit version number\n\n**Pattern:** Numbers are parsed strictly as the first part of the filename before underscore. Files must be properly sorted alphanumerically.\n\n**Command Structure:** Run migrations via:\n- `npm run migrate` — applies pending migrations\n- `npm run migrate:status` — shows applied/pending status\n- `npm start` — automatically runs migrations before starting the server\n\n### Migration System Architecture\n\n**Runner Location:** `migrate.ts` uses `postgres` package (raw SQL with typed results)\n\n**Key Concepts:**\n- Migrations are tracked in a `_migrations` table (version INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ)\n- Each migration runs inside a transaction (atomicity guaranteed)\n- Idempotent: re-running skips already-applied files\n- No down migrations (unidirectional only)\n- Migrations run via `sql.unsafe(content)` + `sql.begin()` for transactional safety\n\n**Startup Flow:**\n```\nnpm start → src/migrate.ts (auto-run) → src/index.ts (server startup)\n```\n\n### SQL Style & Conventions\n\n**Identity Columns:**\n```sql\nBIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY\n```\nUsed instead of BIGSERIAL for explicit generation.\n\n**UUID Columns:**\n```sql\nUUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()\n```\nUsed in referral_claims table.\n\n**Timestamps:**\n```sql\nTIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()  — all timestamps use timezone-aware\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- CHECK constraints on enum TEXT columns for validation (e.g., `CHECK (phase IN ('open', 'settled', 'refunded'))`)\n- Unique constraints with names (e.g., `CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round UNIQUE (...)`)\n- Foreign key relationships NOT used (design pattern: reference by ID text)\n\n**Indexing Patterns:**\n- Filtered indexes for performance: `CREATE INDEX ... WHERE status IN ('pending', 'processing')`\n- Composite indexes for queries: `(user_id, created_at DESC)`\n- BRIN indexes for time-series data: `USING BRIN (minute_ts)`\n- Unique conditional indexes: `CREATE UNIQUE INDEX ... WHERE status IN (...)`\n\n**Example (from 007_game_entries):**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE game_entries (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  wallet          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  game            TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (game IN ('coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')),\n  round_pda       TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  match_id        TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL CHECK (amount_lamports > 0),\n  side            TEXT,\n  is_winner       BOOLEAN,\n  payout_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  UNIQUE (wallet, round_pda)\n);\n```\n\n### Seed Data Patterns\n\n**No seed data exists in migrations.** The project follows these patterns instead:\n\n1. **Auto-creation on first use:** Player profiles are auto-created on first JWT auth via application code (not migrations)\n2. **Event-driven:** Configuration and platform parameters read from on-chain `PlatformConfig` PDA at settlement time (not seeded in DB)\n3. **No INSERT statements:** All 10 migration files use CREATE TABLE/INDEX only—zero INSERT statements\n4. **Dynamic initialization:** Tables like `closecall_candles` and `event_queue` are populated by async workers (pda-watcher, closecall-clock, event-worker) after schema creation\n\n### Database Schema Constants\n\n- **Engine:** PostgreSQL 16\n- **Amounts:** All stored in lamports (u64), conversion to SOL only at display boundaries\n- **User identity:** user_id (TEXT), wallet (TEXT) with separate unique constraints\n- **Rate fields:** Integer basis points (bps) for fees and rates\n- **PDA references:** TEXT (not foreign keys)—matches Solana account addresses\n\n### Summary for Next Migration\n\nWhen creating migration 011, follow this template:\n\n```sql\n-- 011_feature_name.sql — Description of what this adds.\n\nCREATE TABLE [new_table] (\n  id                 BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  [field_name]       TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK ([field_name] IN ('value1', 'value2')),\n  [timestamp_field]  TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  created_at         TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_[table]_[field] ON [new_table] ([field], created_at DESC);\nCREATE INDEX idx_[table]_[field]_filtered ON [new_table] ([field]) WHERE [condition];\n```\n\nKey points: zero-padded version number, CHECK constraints for enums, GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY, TIMESTAMPTZ for all dates, comment header with purpose."}],"totalDurationMs":141065,"totalTokens":46917,"totalToolUseCount":28,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":758,"cache_read_input_tokens":44536,"output_tokens":1616,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":758},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
