{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015TNgtrntinWQaaA5xbR2Rt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the pattern now. The integration test creates certain tables in `beforeAll` that don't come from migrations. These appear to be tables that are needed for the tests but weren't initially created by migrations that the test DB runs.\n\nLooking at this more carefully, the test creates referral tables manually (DROP IF EXISTS + CREATE) in beforeAll. This suggests the test DB gets initialized with migrations up to a certain point but the referral tables (from migration 010) were added manually to the test.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, I think the test DB IS set up by migrations (the server runs migrations on startup, or there's a separate test setup). The referral tables in beforeAll are there because they were added as part of the referral spec implementation and needed to be added to the test file.\n \nThe TRUNCATE in beforeEach is failing because I added `player_points` and related tables to the list, but they don't exist yet since the migration hasn't run. I could manually create them in beforeAll like the referral tables, but it's simpler to just remove them from TRUNCATE for now and add them back once the migration is actually applied and tests start using them.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":782,"cache_read_input_tokens":74605,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":782},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9711a7e-4153-4e8b-be5f-32a94d4f2fda","uuid":"b1860200-e60f-456b-b38c-21538c9db3ea"}
